print-ease (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * The Scan Release. Adds three new scanning workflows: ADF
    hardware duplex (BETA, requires scanner support), multi-page
    flatbed documents (PDF output), and multi-page flatbed archives
    (TIFF output). UI restructured with separate Source and Duplex
    dropdowns plus a new Mode selector.
  * Complete translations across 33 languages: every string in the
    scanner panel, printer-default group, app menu and paper-size
    names is now localised. Previously hardcoded German labels in
    printer defaults and media names are now fully translatable.
  * Fix grammar bugs in agglutinative languages (fi, hu, he) where
    suffixes were appended to placeholder values, producing
    ungrammatical wordforms.

 -- MrHaku81 <haku81.kk@gmail.com>  Sun, 17 May 2026 14:16:00 +0200

print-ease (0.1.6-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add per-printer default settings UI: paper format, duplex, color
    mode and print quality can now be configured directly from the
    printer detail page without needing command-line tools.

 -- MrHaku81 <haku81.kk@gmail.com>  Thu, 07 May 2026 18:30:00 +0200

print-ease (0.1.5-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix hardcoded APP_VERSION constant in constants.py that wasn't
    bumped during the 0.1.4 release. The About dialog now correctly
    displays the installed version.

 -- MrHaku81 <haku81.kk@gmail.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 18:30:00 +0200

print-ease (0.1.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix scanner discovery for printers with self-signed eSCL certificates
    (e.g. Ricoh, Canon, HP AirPrint devices on Ubuntu/Debian where CUPS
    auto-registers them with ipps:// URIs).
  * Upgrade scanner discovery failure log from DEBUG to WARNING for
    better visibility.

 -- MrHaku81 <haku81.kk@gmail.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 15:30:00 +0200

